        <p>The final integral cannot be solved in terms of elementary functions, so we resorted to a numerical approximation. (Simpson's Rule, with <m>n=4</m>, approximates the value with <m>13.0608</m>. Using <m>n=22</m> gives the value above, which is accurate to 4 places after the decimal.)</p>
      </solution>
